                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18420613-1987-offence-1 t18420613-name-1366"></join>Samuel Hall</persName>, from his person.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420613-name-1367" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-1367" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-1367" type="surname" value="HALL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-1367" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>SAMUEL HALL</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a Greenwich pensioner. I was in the Infirmary and got leave to go out for a few hours, on the 19th of May—I went to the Red Lion—I had a pint of beer—I paid one shilling, and had sixpence and four penny-pieces in change—I put my beer down in the parlour, and went into the tap-room to light my pipe—I had then 3<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. in silver, four penny-pieces, and 2 1/2 <hi rend="italic">d</hi>., in a leather purse, in my waistcoat pocket—probably the string might be hanging out, I cannot say—I was not three minutes gone into the tap—I then returned and drank my beer up—I went out, and did not walk above three yards before I missed my purse—I do not know who took it—I am nearly blind.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. BALLANTINE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Are you certain you had the purse when you went in? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—I cannot swear it might not have dropped out of my pocket, but I was not taking any thing out of my pocket—I saw no person near me—I went back to the Infirmary, and on the Sunday following a policeman and Abraham Young came to me.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420613-name-1368" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-1368" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-1368" type="surname" value="YOUNG"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-1368" type="given" value="ABRAHAM"></interp>ABRAHAM YOUNG</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a dustman. I was at the Red Lion that day, and saw the prisoner take the money out of the prosecutor's waist<lb></lb>coat pocket—it was in a leather bag—I did not say any thing to him—there were two or three more persons with him—I do not know when I first gave information of this—he put it into his pocket—I knew two or three <hi rend="italic">chaps</hi> that were there—I heard that one of them had been in Maidstone Goal—I did not see him give any of the money to any person there.</p>
